Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with President Isaac Herzog of Israel and extended Passover greetings. She expressed condolences on behalf of the Biden-Harris Administration for Israeli deaths in recent terrorist attacks and condemned these attacks strongly. Harris emphasized unwavering U.S. support for Israel's security and self-defense and expressed support for efforts to reduce tensions. She reiterated the unshakeable bond between the United States and Israel and the commitment to stay in close touch on issues affecting Israel's security and regional stability.